output_data.summary: Follow-up session assessing partial response to Sertraline and managing severe exacerbation of recurrent Major Depressive Disorder, requiring dose titration.
output_data.reasoning: The session served as a routine follow-up four weeks post-initiation of Sertraline 50mg. Significant clinical decline (including vegetative symptoms and passive suicidal ideation) was noted, necessitating immediate medication dose increase (titration to 100mg) and comprehensive safety assessment.
